summary:
The Security Council:
Recalling previous resolutions on Lebanon, particularly 425 (1978) and 426 (1978), and the statement of its President on 18 June 2000, 
Recalling the letter from its President to the Secretary-General of 18 May 2001 and the Secretary-General's conclusions on Israel's withdrawal from Lebanon,
Emphasizing UNIFIL's interim nature,
Recalling resolutions 1308 (2000) and 1325 (2000) and the Convention on the Safety of United Nations Personnel,
Responding to Lebanon's request, 
Expressing concern over tensions and potential escalation,
 Endorses the Secretary-General's report on UNIFIL and renews its mandate for six months until 31 July 2004; 
Reiterates support for Lebanon's territorial integrity, sovereignty and independence; 
Encourages Lebanon to ensure its effective authority in the south; 
Calls on parties to ensure UNIFIL's freedom of movement; 
Reiterates the call on parties to respect the withdrawal line and exercise restraint; 
Condemns acts of violence and urges parties to abide by their obligations; 
Supports UNIFIL's efforts to maintain the ceasefire; 
Welcomes demining progress and encourages further assistance; 
Requests the Secretary-General to consult with Lebanon and report to the Council; 
Looks forward to UNIFIL's early fulfilment of its mandate; 
Stresses the need for a comprehensive, just and lasting peace in the Middle East.
